Mukherdshi said after the talks that it was difficult for the executive to intervene in judicial matters.
Nevertheless, he argued that in the case of Petr Švácha, who was acquitted of the charges and fined, the central government wanted the local government in Dardjiling, whose jurisdiction covered the matter.
"His problem could be solved," the minister said.
For Emil Kučera, who was sentenced to three years in prison, Mukherdshi believes it would be best if he appealed to a higher court.
